com.helger.jcodemodel

Class AbstractJType

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.helger.jcodemodel.AbstractJType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IJGenerable, IJObject, IJOwned
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractJClass, JPrimitiveType

    public abstract class AbstractJType
extends Object
implements IJGenerable, IJOwned
    A representation of a type in codeModel. A type is always either primitive ( JPrimitiveType) or a reference type (AbstractJClass).
    Note: up to version 2.7.6 this class implemented Comparable <AbstractJType>. Since this was specific to import handling on emitting code, it was removed with 2.7.7!

      • isAssignableFrom

        public boolean isAssignableFrom(@Nonnull
                                AbstractJType aThat)
        Checks the relationship between two types.

        This method performs superset of actions that are performed by Class.isAssignableFrom(Class) For example, baseClass.isAssignableFrom(derivedClass) is always true.

        There are two differences of this method and Class.isAssignableFrom(Class)

        1. This method works with primitive types
        2. This method processes generic arguments and supports wildcards

        Examples:

        1. [[List]].isAssignableFrom ([[List<T>]])
        2. [[List<T>]].isAssignableFrom ([[List]])
        3. [[List<? extends Object>]].isAssignableFrom ([[List<Integer>]])
        4. [[List<? super Serializable>]].isAssignableFrom ([[List<String>]])
        5. [[List<? super Serializable>]].isAssignableFrom ([[List<String>]])
        6. [[List<? extends Object>]].isAssignableFrom ([[List<? extends Integer>]])
        7. [[List<? extends List<? extends Object>>]].isAssignableFrom ([[List<List<Integer>>]])
        Parameters:
        aThat - Type to check
        Returns:
        true if assignable, false if not
